HEADWORD: Perempt
<hw>Per*empt"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>peremptus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>perimere</ets> to take away
entirely, to destroy; <ets>per</ets> (see <er>Per-</er>) + OL.
<ets>emere</ets> to take. See <er>Redeem</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld>
<def>To destroy; to defeat.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Ayliffe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

